Video via https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZT6Qo146Ncs&t=10s

Some strange is happening in Hollywood movies: female characters become masculine, while the masculine is erased. This is neither replacing the masculine by the feminine, nor an androgynous synthesis. What is it then ? Jonathan Pageau is an orthodox icon carver.

=Description=

Jonathan Pageau:

"Disney's Moana is the prime example of the recent trend of replacing masculine imagery with the feminine in movies. 

I offer an interpretation of the the symbolism in Moana and how it plays out the gender ideology that is being inserted into popular culture through media and education."


